headline: Commissioners approve bonds for Coca-Cola building purchase
summary: The Lee County Board of Commissioners voted 5-2 Monday to move forward with financing the purchase of the old Coca-Cola building through limited obligation bonds. Commissioners Andre Knecht and Samantha Martin voted against the resolution which allows the county to enter into a trust agreement and purchase the obligation bonds to finance no more than $7.8 million for the Coca-Cola building. ...

headline: Top Dividend Stocks To Consider In September 2025
summary: As major U.S. indices hit record highs, driven by a surge in technology stocks and strategic investments, the market continues to present intriguing opportunities for investors. In this dynamic environment, dividend stocks remain an attractive option for those seeking steady income and potential growth amid fluctuating interest rates and evolving economic conditions.

headline: Mexico's Femsa appoints Jose Antonio Fernandez Garza-Laguera as CEO
summary: Garza-Laguera, who will replace the interim CEO Antonio Fernandez Carbajal, is currently the CEO of Femsa Proximity & Health and has held several management roles across Femsa's business units.  Carbajal has served as the interim CEO since July 2023 and will continue in his role as an executive chairman, the company said.
